00031 void testFilter(const ScanFilter& scanFilter,
00032                 TriBool accurateMassType,
00033                 TriBool coronaOn,
00034                 TriBool detectorSet,
00035                 TriBool photoIonizationOn,
00036                 TriBool sourceCIDOn,
00037                 TriBool turboScanOn,
00038                 TriBool widebandOn,
00039                 TriBool dependentActive,
00040                 MassAnalyzerType massAnalyzerType,
00041                 PolarityType polarityType,
00042                 DataPointType dataPointType,
00043                 IonizationType ionizationType,
00044                 ScanType scanType,
00045                 int msLevel,
00046                 const vector<double>& cidParentMass,
00047                 const vector<double>& cidParentEnergy,
00048                 const vector<double>& scanRangeMin,
00049                 const vector<double>& scanRangeMax )
00050 {
00051     unit_assert(scanFilter.accurateMassType_ == accurateMassType);
00052     unit_assert(scanFilter.coronaOn_ == coronaOn);
00053     unit_assert(scanFilter.detectorSet_ == detectorSet);
00054     unit_assert(scanFilter.photoIonizationOn_ == photoIonizationOn);
00055     unit_assert(scanFilter.sourceCIDOn_ == sourceCIDOn);
00056     unit_assert(scanFilter.turboScanOn_ == turboScanOn);
00057     unit_assert(scanFilter.widebandOn_ == widebandOn);
00058     unit_assert(scanFilter.dependentActive_ == dependentActive);
00059 
00060     unit_assert(scanFilter.massAnalyzerType_ == massAnalyzerType);
00061     unit_assert(scanFilter.polarityType_ == polarityType);
00062     unit_assert(scanFilter.dataPointType_ == dataPointType);
00063     unit_assert(scanFilter.ionizationType_ == ionizationType);
00064     unit_assert(scanFilter.scanType_ == scanType);
00065 
00066     unit_assert(scanFilter.msLevel_ == msLevel);
00067     unit_assert(scanFilter.cidParentMass_.size() == scanFilter.cidEnergy_.size() &&
00068                 cidParentMass.size() == cidParentEnergy.size() &&
00069                 scanFilter.cidEnergy_.size() == cidParentMass.size());
00070     unit_assert(cidParentMass.size() == (size_t) scanFilter.msLevel_-1);
00071     for (int i=0; i < scanFilter.msLevel_-1; ++i)
00072     {
00073         unit_assert(scanFilter.cidParentMass_[i] == cidParentMass[i] && scanFilter.cidEnergy_[i] == cidParentEnergy[i]);
00074     }
00075 
00076     unit_assert(scanFilter.scanRangeMin_.size() == scanFilter.scanRangeMax_.size() &&
00077                 scanRangeMin.size() == scanRangeMax.size() &&
00078                 scanFilter.scanRangeMin_.size() == scanRangeMin.size());
00079     if (scanType == ScanType_Full || scanType == ScanType_Zoom) // TODO: which scan types can have more than one range?
00080         unit_assert(scanRangeMin.size() == 1);
00081 
00082     for (size_t i=0; i < scanFilter.scanRangeMin_.size(); ++i)
00083     {
00084         unit_assert(scanFilter.scanRangeMin_[i] == scanRangeMin[i] &&
00085                     scanFilter.scanRangeMax_[i] == scanRangeMax[i]);
00086     }
00087 }
